{"type":"message","id":"e9bdcf51","parentId":"bf20868d","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:16:01.990Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so it works with the full qualified name. The issue is:\n1. Entity extraction from natural language is unreliable - it needs exact matches or very close ones\n2. The resolution logic tries various approaches but doesn't always find the right node\n\nThe next steps from the memory were:\n1. Fix query engine entity extraction \n2. Dynamic tracer\n\nLet me focus on improving the entity extraction first - making it smarter about extracting entities from partial names, filenames, and casual phrasing.\n\nThe core issues are:\n1. `_extract_entity` only handles: quoted strings, \"of X\" pattern, \"change X\" pattern\n2. `_resolve_entity` does normalization and suffix matching but the extraction fails before resolution even happens\n\n\n3. A simple fix would be to handle filenames like \"attention.py\" → look for module names containing \"attention\", and make suffix matching more aggressive so partial class names can still resolve properly\n\nLet me implement these improvements.","thinkingSignature":"be2a123f0d92858e6b615c3e7e7675728ade24e4364828e75c39ee1addebcbba"},{"type":"text","text":"Query engine works with full qualified names but entity extraction from casual phrasing is weak — \"attention.py\" or \"TemporalOnly\" won't resolve. That's the next fix. Let me improve it:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kzpnqe3wy0ix_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":1,"limit":80,"file_path":"C:/dev/code-cause/src/causal_indexer/query_engine.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":9620,"output":287,"cacheRead":12619,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22526,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774221354144}}
{"type":"message","id":"d49d3da7","parentId":"e9bdcf51","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:16:02.004Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_kzpnqe3wy0ix_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nQuery Engine\n============\nHigh-level causal queries over the dependency graph.\n\nProvides natural-language-style queries that map to graph traversals,\nplus ranking/filtering of results.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom typing import Optional\nfrom .graph_builder import CausalGraph\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass CausalResult:\n    \"\"\"A single result from a causal query.\"\"\"\n    entity: str\n    kind: str\n    file_path: str\n    lineno: int\n    docstring: Optional[str]\n    score: float            # importance/relevance score\n    path: list[str]        # causal path from query root to this entity\n    reason: str            # human-readable explanation of why this matters\n\n\nclass QueryEngine:\n    \"\"\"\n    Causal query interface for a codebase graph.\n\n    Example:\n        engine = QueryEngine(graph)\n        results = engine.query(\"what happens if I change auth.py validate_token?\")\n        for r in results:\n            print(f\"{r.entity} (score={r.score:.2f}): {r.reason}\")\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, graph: CausalGraph):\n        self.graph = graph\n\n    def query(self, question: str, top_k: int = 10) -> list[CausalResult]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Parse a natural-ish question and execute the corresponding causal query.\n\n        Supported question patterns:\n        - \"what happens if I change X?\" / \"what does X affect?\" / \"impact of X\"\n        - \"what caused X?\" / \"what does X depend on?\" / \"causes of X\"\n        - \"what uses X?\" / \"who calls X?\" / \"dependents of X\"\n        - \"ripple effect of X\" / \"full impact of X\"\n        \"\"\"\n        q = question.lower()\n\n        # Extract entity name from quotes or \"of X\" pattern\n        entity = self._extract_entity(q)\n\n        # \"what calls X\" / \"who uses X\" → dependents (who depends on X)\n        if any(k in q for k in [\"calls\", \"who calls\", \"who use\", \"what calls\", \"dependents\", \"who depend\"]):\n            return self._query_dependents(entity, top_k)\n        # \"what does X affect\" / \"what will break if X changes\" → impact (what X touches)\n        elif any(k in q for k in [\"affect\", \"ripple\", \"break\", \"what will\", \"happens if\"]):\n            return self._query_impact(entity, top_k)\n        # \"what does X depend on\" / \"what caused X\" → causes (what X needs)\n        elif any(k in q for k in [\"caus\", \"depend on\", \"prereq\", \"needed\", \"require\"]):\n            return self._query_causes(entity, top_k)\n        else:\n            # Default to impact query\n            return self._query_impact(entity, top_k)\n\n    def _extract_entity(self, question: str) -> Optional[str]:\n        \"\"\"Extract the entity being asked about from the question text.\"\"\"\n        import re\n\n        # Match quoted strings: \"auth.validate_token\" or 'auth.validate_token'\n        quoted = re.findall(r'[\"\\']([^\"\\']+)[\"\\']', question)\n        if quoted:\n            return quoted[0]\n\n\n[241 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774221361998}}
{"type":"message","id":"2acfa3f7","parentId":"d49d3da7","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:16:17.406Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me improve `_extract_entity` to handle more patterns, and `_resolve_entity` to be smarter about matching. The main improvements:\n\n1. `_extract_entity` needs to handle:\n   - `change X` / `modify X` (already done but limited)\n   - bare words that might be class/function names (try last component matching)\n   - filenames like `attention.py` → extract module name\n\n2. `_resolve_entity` needs to:\n   - Handle case-insensitive prefix matching on last component\n   - When nothing matches, try fuzzy matching on the last path component\n\nLet me rewrite these two methods.","thinkingSignature":"664bff660c80ccbad84aff8089f8114615623054407499fada505a670d873416"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jjh2ssdf1xxo_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"C:/dev/code-cause/src/causal_indexer/query_engine.py","old_string":"    def _extract_entity(self, question: str) -> Optional[str]:\n        \"\"\"Extract the entity being asked about from the question text.\"\"\"\n        import re\n\n        # Match quoted strings: \"auth.validate_token\" or 'auth.validate_token'\n        quoted = re.findall(r'[\"\\']([^\"\\']+)[\"\\']', question)\n        if quoted:\n            return quoted[0]\n\n        # Match \"of X\" pattern: \"of auth.validate_token\"\n        of_match = re.search(r'\\bof\\s+([\\w.]+)', question)\n        if of_match:\n            return of_match.group(1)\n\n        # Match \"change X\" / \"modify X\" / \"affect X\"\n        modify_match = re.search(r'(?:change|modify|affect|update|edit)\\s+([\\w.]+)', question)\n        if modify_match:\n            return modify_match.group(1)\n\n        return None","new_string":"    def _extract_entity(self, question: str) -> Optional[str]:\n        \"\"\"Extract the entity being asked about from the question text.\"\"\"\n        import re\n\n        # Match quoted strings: \"auth.validate_token\" or 'auth.validate_token'\n        quoted = re.findall(r'[\"\\']([^\"\\']+)[\"\\']', question)\n        if quoted:\n            return quoted[0]\n\n        # Match \"of X\" pattern: \"of auth.validate_token\"\n        of_match = re.search(r'\\bof\\s+([\\w.]+)', question)\n        if of_match:\n            return of_match.group(1)\n\n        # Match \"change X\" / \"modify X\" / \"affect X\" / \"update X\" / \"edit X\"\n        modify_match = re.search(r'(?:change|modify|affect|update|edit)\\s+([\\w.]+)', question)\n        if modify_match:\n            return modify_match.group(1)\n\n        # Strip common question prefixes and extract the main subject\n        # e.g. \"what uses AttentionLayer?\" → AttentionLayer\n        stripped = question\n        for prefix in [\"what happens if i \", \"what if i \", \"what will break if i \",\n                       \"what does \", \"what uses \", \"what calls \", \"who calls \",\n                       \"who uses \", \"what should i \", \"if i change \", \"i change \"]:\n            if stripped.startswith(prefix):\n                stripped = stripped[len(prefix):]\n                break\n\n        # Clean up trailing punctuation and common suffixes\n        stripped = re.sub(r'[?!.].*$', '', stripped)  # remove trailing punctuation\n        stripped = re.sub(r'\\s+(function|class|method|module).*$', '', stripped)\n        stripped = stripped.strip()\n\n        # If we have a bare identifier or path-like fragment, return it\n        if stripped and re.match(r'^[\\w./\\\\-]+$', stripped):\n            return stripped\n\n        return None"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":10635,"output":785,"cacheRead":12619,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24039,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774221362005}}
{"type":"message","id":"e5a65db8","parentId":"2acfa3f7","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:16:17.424Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_jjh2ssdf1xxo_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:/dev/code-cause/src/causal_indexer/query_engine.py."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  82         of_match = re.search(r'\\bof\\s+([\\w.]+)', question)\n  83         if of_match:\n  84             return of_match.group(1)\n  85 \n- 86         # Match \"change X\" / \"modify X\" / \"affect X\"\n+ 86         # Match \"change X\" / \"modify X\" / \"affect X\" / \"update X\" / \"edit X\"\n  87         modify_match = re.search(r'(?:change|modify|affect|update|edit)\\s+([\\w.]+)', question)\n  88         if modify_match:\n  89             return modify_match.group(1)\n  90 \n+ 91         # Strip common question prefixes and extract the main subject\n+ 92         # e.g. \"what uses AttentionLayer?\" → AttentionLayer\n+ 93         stripped = question\n+ 94         for prefix in [\"what happens if i \", \"what if i \", \"what will break if i \",\n+ 95                        \"what does \", \"what uses \", \"what calls \", \"who calls \",\n+ 96                        \"who uses \", \"what should i \", \"if i change \", \"i change \"]:\n+ 97             if stripped.startswith(prefix):\n+ 98                 stripped = stripped[len(prefix):]\n+ 99                 break\n+100 \n+101         # Clean up trailing punctuation and common suffixes\n+102         stripped = re.sub(r'[?!.].*$', '', stripped)  # remove trailing punctuation\n+103         stripped = re.sub(r'\\s+(function|class|method|module).*$', '', stripped)\n+104         stripped = stripped.strip()\n+105 \n+106         # If we have a bare identifier or path-like fragment, return it\n+107         if stripped and re.match(r'^[\\w./\\\\-]+$', stripped):\n+108             return stripped\n+109 \n  91         return None\n  92 \n  93     def _score_result(self, name: str, depth: int, is_interface: bool, edge_kind: str) -> float:\n  94         \"\"\"\n     ...","firstChangedLine":86},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774221377419}}
{"type":"message","id":"7dac65f4","parentId":"e5a65db8","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:16:29.030Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me improve `_resolve_entity` to be smarter about fuzzy matching on the last component.","thinkingSignature":"fcb707ae467e48e0eba109095296b60355e66bf1aa0e8e243e23706c6cdc4f1a"},{"type":"text","text":"Now improve `_resolve_entity` to handle partial/fuzzy matches:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h0izthja2wl4_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"C:/dev/code-cause/src/causal_indexer/query_engine.py","old_string":"    def _resolve_entity(self, entity: str) -> Optional[str]:\n        \"\"\"Resolve a partial name to a fully qualified name.\"\"\"\n        # Strip leading dot if present\n        entity = entity.lstrip(\".\")\n\n        # Normalize underscores/hyphens\n        entity_norm = entity.replace(\"-\", \"_\")\n\n        if entity in self.graph.nodes:\n            return entity\n\n        # Try case-insensitive match with normalization\n        lower = entity_norm.lower()\n        for name in self.graph.nodes:\n            if name.replace(\"-\", \"_\").lower() == lower:\n                return name\n\n        # Try suffix match with dot boundary\n        for name in self.graph.nodes:\n            if name.endswith(\".\" + entity) or name == entity:\n                return name\n\n        # Try normalized suffix match\n        for name in self.graph.nodes:\n            name_norm = name.replace(\"-\", \"_\")\n            if name_norm.endswith(\".\" + entity_norm) or name_norm == entity_norm:\n                return name\n\n        # Try last-component match\n        parts = entity.split(\".\")\n        for name in self.graph.nodes:\n            if name.endswith(parts[-1]):\n                return name\n\n        return None","new_string":"    def _resolve_entity(self, entity: str) -> Optional[str]:\n        \"\"\"Resolve a partial name to a fully qualified name.\"\"\"\n        # Strip leading dot if present\n        entity = entity.lstrip(\".\")\n\n        # Normalize underscores/hyphens\n        entity_norm = entity.replace(\"-\", \"_\")\n\n        # Strip common filename extensions\n        if entity_norm.endswith(\".py\"):\n            entity_norm = entity_norm[:-3]\n        if \"/\" in entity_norm or \"\\\\\" in entity_norm:\n            # It's a file path — extract just the filename without extension\n            import re\n            entity_norm = re.sub(r'[/\\\\].*$', '', entity_norm)\n\n        if entity_norm in self.graph.nodes:\n            return entity_norm\n\n        # Try case-insensitive exact match with normalization\n        lower = entity_norm.lower()\n        for name in self.graph.nodes:\n            if name.replace(\"-\", \"_\").lower() == lower:\n                return name\n\n        # Try suffix match with dot boundary\n        for name in self.graph.nodes:\n            if name.endswith(\".\" + entity) or name == entity:\n                return name\n\n        # Try normalized suffix match\n        for name in self.graph.nodes:\n            name_norm = name.replace(\"-\", \"_\")\n            if name_norm.endswith(\".\" + entity_norm) or name_norm == entity_norm:\n                return name\n\n        # Try last-component match (e.g. \"TemporalOnly\" → \"...TemporalOnly\")\n        last = entity_norm.split(\".\")[-1]\n        candidates = []\n        for name in self.graph.nodes:\n            name_norm = name.replace(\"-\", \"_\")\n            # Case-insensitive last-component match\n            if name_norm.split(\".\")[-1].lower() == last.lower():\n                candidates.append(name)\n\n        if len(candidates) == 1:\n            return candidates[0]\n        elif len(candidates) > 1:\n            # Prefer the shortest match (most specific)\n            candidates.sort(key=len)\n            return candidates[0]\n\n        return None"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":11453,"output":736,"cacheRead":12619,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24808,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774221377425}}
