{"type":"message","id":"b1f25aa9","parentId":"7ba2b635","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:19:42.580Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that `_extract_entity` returns `None` for `\"what does ScoringConfig affect\"`. The pattern \"what does X affect\" - let me trace through:\n\n1. `stripped = \"what does scoringconfig affect\"`\n2. It doesn't start with any of the prefixes\n3. `re.sub(r'[?!.].*$', '', stripped)` → \"what does scoringconfig affect\" (no punctuation)\n4. `re.sub(r'\\s+(function|class|method|module).*$', '', stripped)` → same (no suffix)\n5. `re.match(r'^[\\w./\\\\-]+$', stripped)` → False because of \"what does \" prefix\n\n\n6. So `_extract_entity` returns `None`\n\nThe problem is my extraction logic only handles \"what happens if I change X\" but not \"what does X affect\". I need to handle query patterns like \"what does X affect\", \"what will X break\", \"who calls X\", and \"what uses X\" by extracting the entity from the middle of the question rather than just from the beginning.\n\nFor \"what does ScoringConfig affect\", after stripping the prefix I get \"ScoringConfig\". For \"what uses TemporalOnly?\", stripping gives \"TemporalOnly\". But \"what happens if I change TemporalOnly?\" should also yield \"TemporalOnly\" once I remove that initial prefix.\n\nLooking back at my prefix list, I had \"what does \" but I need to verify the order and completeness of the patterns I'm stripping. I'm checking the prefix removal logic—the first matching prefix gets stripped, so for \"what does ScoringConfig affect\", it should remove \"what does \" and leave \"ScoringConfig affect\", but then my regex pattern `[\\w./\\\\-]+` fails because it doesn't account for the remaining words after the entity name. The issue is that my pattern expects the entire remaining string to be just the entity, but real queries have additional words like \"affect\" that break the match. I need to extract just the entity name from the beginning of the stripped string instead of requiring the whole thing to match the pattern.","thinkingSignature":"235a0d744140898c87f1440eca50673a89cf2b1d8b6c87466eb37a34318f4baa"},{"type":"text","text":"The entity extraction fails for \"what does X affect\" because \"ScoringConfig affect\" doesn't match `[\\w./\\\\-]+`. Let me fix the extraction to grab only the entity identifier from the front:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f3v1twa0ky60_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"C:/dev/code-cause/src/causal_indexer/query_engine.py","old_string":"        # Clean up trailing punctuation and common suffixes\n        stripped = re.sub(r'[?!.].*$', '', stripped)  # remove trailing punctuation\n        stripped = re.sub(r'\\s+(function|class|method|module).*$', '', stripped)\n        stripped = stripped.strip()\n\n        # If we have a bare identifier or path-like fragment, return it\n        if stripped and re.match(r'^[\\w./\\\\-]+$', stripped):\n            return stripped\n\n        return None","new_string":"        # Clean up trailing punctuation and common suffixes\n        stripped = re.sub(r'[?!.].*$', '', stripped)  # remove trailing punctuation\n        stripped = re.sub(r'\\s+(function|class|method|module).*$', '', stripped)\n        stripped = stripped.strip()\n\n        # If it looks like a bare identifier or path, return it directly\n        if stripped and re.match(r'^[\\w./\\\\-]+$', stripped):\n            return stripped\n\n        # Otherwise extract the first identifier-like fragment (handles \"ScoringConfig affect\")\n        first_ident = re.match(r'^([\\w./\\\\-]+)', stripped)\n        if first_ident:\n            return first_ident.group(1)\n\n        return None"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":18452,"output":781,"cacheRead":12619,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31852,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp