{"type":"message","id":"0db8ef67","parentId":"c4df6a0d","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:23:33.913Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check the test file to see what it does:","thinkingSignature":"e2b3ffe3b53f56b769639938f6b97f03d59db53d612c77be4ae90a90742d4365"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tr7ojw2q3ndl_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:/dev/code-cause/test_dynamic_tracer.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":28813,"output":48,"cacheRead":12619,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41480,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774221811046}}
{"type":"message","id":"4b70b21f","parentId":"0db8ef67","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:23:33.942Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tr7ojw2q3ndl_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\ntest_dynamic_tracer.py\nTest the dynamic tracer on the causal indexer itself.\n\"\"\"\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nsys.path.insert(0, str(Path(__file__).parent / \"src\"))\nsys.path.insert(0, str(Path(__file__).parent))\n\nfrom causal_indexer import DynamicTracer, QueryEngine, StaticAnalyzer, CausalGraph\n\n\ndef test_on_causal_indexer():\n    \"\"\"Trace the causal indexer analyzing itself.\"\"\"\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n    print(\"DynamicTracer test: tracing the causal indexer\")\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n\n    with DynamicTracer(str(Path(__file__).parent / \"src\" / \"causal_indexer\")) as tracer:\n        analyzer = StaticAnalyzer(str(Path(__file__).parent / \"src\" / \"causal_indexer\"))\n        analyzer.analyze()\n        graph = CausalGraph.from_analysis(analyzer.definitions, analyzer.references)\n\n    stats = tracer.stats()\n    print(f\"\\nTrace stats: {stats}\")\n\n    # Build graph from trace\n    trace_graph = tracer.build_graph()\n    gstats = trace_graph.stats()\n    print(f\"Trace graph: {gstats['total_nodes']} nodes, {gstats['total_edges']} edges\")\n\n    # Top functions by call count (incoming edges)\n    print(\"\\nTop 15 most-called functions:\")\n    node_edges = []\n    for name in trace_graph.nodes:\n        inc = len(trace_graph._incoming.get(name, []))\n        out = len(trace_graph._outgoing.get(name, []))\n        node_edges.append((name, inc, out))\n    node_edges.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n    for name, inc, out in node_edges[:15]:\n        print(f\"  {inc:3d} in / {out:3d} out  {name}\")\n\n    # Causal query test\n    print(\"\\nQuery: what does StaticAnalyzer.analyze affect?\")\n    engine = QueryEngine(trace_graph)\n    results = engine.query(\"what does StaticAnalyzer.analyze affect\")\n    print(f\"  {len(results)} results\")\n    for r in results[:5]:\n        print(f\"    [{r.kind}] {r.entity}\")\n\n    # Query: what calls CausalGraph.from_analysis\n    print(\"\\nQuery: what calls CausalGraph.from_analysis?\")\n    results = engine.query(\"what calls CausalGraph.from_analysis\")\n    print(f\"  {len(results)} results\")\n    for r in results[:5]:\n        print(f\"    [{r.kind}] {r.entity}\")\n\n    output = str(Path(__file__).parent / \"data\" / \"causal_indexer_trace.json\")\n    Path(output).parent.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n    trace_graph.save(output)\n    print(f\"\\nSaved: {output}\")\n    return trace_graph\n\n\ndef test_on_exp_production():\n    \"\"\"Trace the EXP production core module.\"\"\"\n    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 60)\n    print(\"DynamicTracer test: tracing EXP production/core\")\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n\n    exp_core = \"C:/dev/EXP/production/core\"\n    if not Path(exp_core).exists():\n        print(\"EXP production/core not found, skipping\")\n        return\n\n    sys.path.insert(0, \"C:/dev/EXP/production\")\n\n    with DynamicTracer(exp_core) as tracer:\n        try:\n            from production.core.execution import ExecutionEngine\n            from production.core.memory import BlockAllocator\n\n            # Run some operations\n            alloc = BlockAllocator()\n            # Minimal operations just to trigger some calls\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"Import/run error: {e}\")\n\n    stats = tracer.stats()\n    print(f\"\\nTrace stats: {stats}\")\n\n    trace_graph = tracer.build_graph()\n    gstats = trace_graph.stats()\n    print(f\"Trace graph: {gstats['total_nodes']} nodes, {gstats['total_edges']} edges\")\n\n    if gstats['total_nodes'] > 0:\n        print(\"\\nTop 10 most-called functions:\")\n        node_edges = []\n        for name in trace_graph.nodes:\n            inc = len(trace_graph._incoming.get(name, []))\n            node_edges.append((name, inc))\n        node_edges.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n        for name, inc in node_edges[:10]:\n            print(f\"  {inc:3d}  {name}\")\n\n    output = str(Path(__file__).parent / \"data\" / \"exp_trace.json\")\n    Path(output).parent.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n    trace_graph.save(output)\n    print(f\"\\nSaved: {output}\")\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    test_on_causal_indexer()\n    test_on_exp_production()\n    print(\"\\nAll tests done!\")\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774221813933}}
{"type":"message","id":"4dda60ec","parentId":"4b70b21f","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:23:46.613Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The test traces the causal indexer itself, which involves `StaticAnalyzer.analyze()` and `CausalGraph.from_analysis()`. The issue might be that tracing the tracer's own module causes infinite recursion or a very long trace.\n\nActually, looking at the test — it traces the causal indexer's own source directory, but then ALSO imports and runs the StaticAnalyzer from that same directory. The tracer traces ALL function calls in the codebase, which could be many thousands for a full analysis.\n\nThe `max_events` is 100,000 which should be enough... but maybe it's just slow. Let me kill the process and look at the issue differently.\n\nActually wait — looking more carefully, the test runs `analyzer.analyze()` and `CausalGraph.from_analysis()`. \n\nI think the real problem is that the tracer is capturing function calls and returns from the tracer's own internals, which creates a tangled mess of nested calls. I should either filter out the tracer's code from the trace or skip the dynamic tracer test entirely and focus on the query engine improvements instead.","thinkingSignature":"158b3f051c703d4914c536a48d180b977c93c8186c9693e8588b8cecab855929"},{"type":"text","text":"The dynamic tracer test is hanging — likely tracing its own module causing deep recursion. Let me kill and focus on what's working:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8906u8zabdux_1","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"kill","sessionId":"mellow-bloom"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":29888,"output":281,"cacheRead":12619,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42788,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774221813945}}
