{"type":"message","id":"cc10bc22","parentId":"ac87d569","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:24:17.188Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `TemporalAttentionStore` has no outgoing edges in the static analysis graph — meaning the analyzer doesn't capture what methods/functions it calls. This is expected since the analyzer is looking at AST-level imports and references, not runtime method calls.\n\nAnd `Window` resolves but has no impacts. Let me check what Window actually maps to:","thinkingSignature":"34264e8628b6caf26352fc3ad5409187e7ba94175659b723e82d97365367f0bb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5t597vnczl1y_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:/dev/code-cause && python -c \"\nimport sys; sys.path.insert(0, 'src')\nfrom causal_indexer import StaticAnalyzer, CausalGraph\n\nanalyzer = StaticAnalyzer('C:/dev/temporal-attention')\nanalyzer.analyze()\ngraph = CausalGraph.from_analysis(analyzer.definitions, analyzer.references)\n\n# Check what Window resolves to\nmatches = [n for n in graph.nodes if 'window' in n.lower()]\nprint('Window matches:', matches[:10])\n\n# Check incoming/outgoing for TemporalAttentionStore\ntas = 'TemporalAttentionStore'\nprint('Incoming:', graph._incoming.get(tas, [])[:10])\nprint('Outgoing:', graph._outgoing.get(tas, []))\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":31412,"output":248,"cacheRead":12619,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44279,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774221851260}}
