{"type":"message","id":"374e309b","parentId":"354c564f","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:24:28.963Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so `TemporalAttentionStore` has incoming edges (things that call it), but no outgoing edges. The static analyzer captures imports/calls but not what a class does internally (its method implementations). This is a known limitation.\n\n`Window` resolves to the bare `Window` class, but it has no outgoing edges either (just class definition, no method implementations tracked).\n\nThese are fundamental static analysis limitations — the analyzer captures \"who references who\" at the import/function call level, but not intra-procedural relationships (what happens inside a function body).\n\nThe dynamic tracer would capture actual runtime call graphs, which would show `TemporalAttentionStore` calling methods on other objects.\n\n\nI should wrap up the query engine work I've done and summarize what's been improved for Zach — the entity extraction now handles more patterns, the resolver prefers non-external nodes, and the impact query deduplicates results. The core limitations around intra-procedural analysis are expected and would be addressed by the dynamic tracer approach.\n\nLet me check if the dynamic tracer has the same recursion issue when tracing the causal indexer itself — I need to filter out the tracer's own code to prevent it from getting caught in its own net.","thinkingSignature":"35702f1cc2f79ce2663381825403367df7e2288efbca6e1b81e7b345f052869a"},{"type":"text","text":"The zero-result queries are expected — static analysis captures cross-module edges but not intra-class method calls. That's precisely why the dynamic tracer exists (captures runtime call graphs). The tracer needs a self-exclusion filter though to avoid tracing itself. Let me fix that:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_z174ig1yylda_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":120,"limit":30,"file_path":"C:/dev/code-cause/src/causal_indexer/dynamic_tracer.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":31802,"output":356,"cacheRead":12619,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44777,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774221859119}}
{"type":"message","id":"ebbd364c","parentId":"374e309b","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:24:28.981Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_z174ig1yylda_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"                if event == \"call\":\n                    tracer._on_call(frame, func_name, qual_name, filepath, lineno)\n                elif event == \"return\":\n                    tracer._on_return(frame, func_name, qual_name, filepath, lineno, arg)\n                elif event == \"exception\":\n                    tracer._on_exception(frame, func_name, filepath, lineno, arg)\n            except Exception:\n                pass  # never let tracer crash the traced program\n\n            return trace_func\n\n        return trace_func\n\n    def _is_local(self, filepath: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Check if a file belongs to the target codebase.\"\"\"\n        if not filepath:\n            return False\n        try:\n            # Resolve to absolute and check prefix\n            abs_path = Path(filepath).resolve()\n            # Check if path is under codebase root\n            try:\n                abs_path.relative_to(self.codebase_root)\n                return True\n            except ValueError:\n                return False\n        except Exception:\n            return False\n\n    def _get_module_qualname(self, frame) -> str:\n\n[198 more lines in file. Use offset=150 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774221868975}}
