{"type":"message","id":"8948cde3","parentId":"f0b80655","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:24:39.654Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, that's not quite right. I need to actually use `tracer_files` in the trace_func to skip tracing the tracer itself. Let me rethink this.\n\nThe trace_func is defined inside `_make_trace_func`. I need to skip frames that are part of the tracer module itself. Let me do this properly:","thinkingSignature":"75c043d8fd22d677cd5d77843bec7dcb7f5f7a67e6a2632a580ba84a5c782ad9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_11sa8nww3o1i_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":90,"limit":80,"file_path":"C:/dev/code-cause/src/causal_indexer/dynamic_tracer.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":32800,"output":125,"cacheRead":12619,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45544,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774221875776}}
{"type":"message","id":"870a24fd","parentId":"8948cde3","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:24:39.672Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_11sa8nww3o1i_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"        self.returns: list[ReturnEvent] = []\n        self.errors: list[tuple[str, str, int]] = []  # (func, error, lineno)\n\n        self._local_modules: set[str] = set()\n        self._last_trace_line: tuple[str, int] = (\"\", 0)\n\n    # ─── Tracing ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n    def _make_trace_func(self):\n        \"\"\"Create the trace function (must be a closure for self reference).\"\"\"\n        tracer = self  # capture reference\n\n        def trace_func(frame, event, arg):\n            if not tracer._active:\n                return trace_func\n            if len(tracer.events) >= tracer.max_events:\n                return trace_func\n\n            try:\n                code = frame.f_code\n                func_name = code.co_name\n                qual_name = code.co_qualname if hasattr(code, 'co_qualname') else func_name\n                filepath = code.co_filename\n                lineno = frame.f_lineno\n\n                # Filter to codebase (or external if enabled)\n                is_local = tracer._is_local(filepath)\n                if not is_local and not tracer.include_external:\n                    return trace_func\n\n                if event == \"call\":\n                    tracer._on_call(frame, func_name, qual_name, filepath, lineno)\n                elif event == \"return\":\n                    tracer._on_return(frame, func_name, qual_name, filepath, lineno, arg)\n                elif event == \"exception\":\n                    tracer._on_exception(frame, func_name, filepath, lineno, arg)\n            except Exception:\n                pass  # never let tracer crash the traced program\n\n            return trace_func\n\n        # Precompute tracer's own file paths to exclude from tracing\n        tracer_files = {\n            str(Path(__file__).resolve()),\n            str(Path(__file__).resolve().parent),\n        }\n\n        return trace_func\n\n    def _is_local(self, filepath: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Check if a file belongs to the target codebase.\"\"\"\n        if not filepath:\n            return False\n        try:\n            # Resolve to absolute and check prefix\n            abs_path = Path(filepath).resolve()\n            # Check if path is under codebase root\n            try:\n                abs_path.relative_to(self.codebase_root)\n                return True\n            except ValueError:\n                return False\n        except Exception:\n            return False\n\n    def _get_module_qualname(self, frame) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Derive a module.qualname from frame globals.\"\"\"\n        module = frame.f_globals.get(\"__name__\", \"\")\n        qualname = frame.f_code.co_name\n        if hasattr(frame.f_code, 'co_qualname'):\n            qn = frame.f_code.co_qualname\n            if qn:\n                return qn\n        if module:\n            # Try to detect class method\n            self_local = frame.f_locals.get(\"self\", None)\n            if self_local:\n                class_name = type(self_local).__name__\n                return f\"{module}.{class_name}.{qualname}\"\n            return f\"{module}.{qualname}\"\n\n[184 more lines in file. Use offset=170 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774221879665}}
{"type":"message","id":"df08f13d","parentId":"870a24fd","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:24:51.431Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that the `tracer_files` assignment is placed after the `return trace_func` statement, which means it's unreachable code. I need to fix this properly. Let me rewrite the `_make_trace_func` to exclude tracer files:","thinkingSignature":"4b74bd58e76dc47bb34493b75b023dd8e662c6b3d6d2295dff5987c8be6906c3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9hagq1pjr4xd_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"C:/dev/code-cause/src/causal_indexer/dynamic_tracer.py","old_string":"    # ─── Tracing ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n    def _make_trace_func(self):\n        \"\"\"Create the trace function (must be a closure for self reference).\"\"\"\n        tracer = self  # capture reference\n\n        def trace_func(frame, event, arg):\n            if not tracer._active:\n                return trace_func\n            if len(tracer.events) >= tracer.max_events:\n                return trace_func\n\n            try:\n                code = frame.f_code\n                func_name = code.co_name\n                qual_name = code.co_qualname if hasattr(code, 'co_qualname') else func_name\n                filepath = code.co_filename\n                lineno = frame.f_lineno\n\n                # Filter to codebase (or external if enabled)\n                is_local = tracer._is_local(filepath)\n                if not is_local and not tracer.include_external:\n                    return trace_func\n\n                if event == \"call\":\n                    tracer._on_call(frame, func_name, qual_name, filepath, lineno)\n                elif event == \"return\":\n                    tracer._on_return(frame, func_name, qual_name, filepath, lineno, arg)\n                elif event == \"exception\":\n                    tracer._on_exception(frame, func_name, filepath, lineno, arg)\n            except Exception:\n                pass  # never let tracer crash the traced program\n\n            return trace_func\n\n        # Precompute tracer's own file paths to exclude from tracing\n        tracer_files = {\n            str(Path(__file__).resolve()),\n            str(Path(__file__).resolve().parent),\n        }\n\n        return trace_func","new_string":"    # ─── Tracing ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n    def _make_trace_func(self):\n        \"\"\"Create the trace function (must be a closure for self reference).\"\"\"\n        tracer = self  # capture reference\n        # Precompute tracer's own file path to exclude from tracing\n        tracer_filepath = str(Path(__file__).resolve())\n\n        def trace_func(frame, event, arg):\n            if not tracer._active:\n                return trace_func\n            if len(tracer.events) >= tracer.max_events:\n                return trace_func\n\n            try:\n                code = frame.f_code\n                func_name = code.co_name\n                qual_name = code.co_qualname if hasattr(code, 'co_qualname') else func_name\n                filepath = code.co_filename\n                lineno = frame.f_lineno\n\n                # Skip tracing the tracer itself\n                if filepath == tracer_filepath:\n                    return trace_func\n\n                # Filter to codebase (or external if enabled)\n                is_local = tracer._is_local(filepath)\n                if not is_local and not tracer.include_external:\n                    return trace_func\n\n                if event == \"call\":\n                    tracer._on_call(frame, func_name, qual_name, filepath, lineno)\n                elif event == \"return\":\n                    tracer._on_return(frame, func_name, qual_name, filepath, lineno, arg)\n                elif event == \"exception\":\n                    tracer._on_exception(frame, func_name, filepath, lineno, arg)\n            except Exception:\n                pass  # never let tracer crash the traced program\n\n            return trace_func\n\n        return trace_func"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":33596,"output":756,"cacheRead":12619,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46971,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774221879675}}
