hangs even with self-exclusion (sys.settrace on Windows may have issues)\n- `what does X affect?` on EXP sometimes returns 0 if target has no outgoing edges in static graph (expected — static analysis misses intra-class calls)\n- Intra-module edges not tracked at method granularity\n\n**Commits:** `3a3fc77` query_engine fixes + new dynamic_tracer.py\n\n**Next for CodeCause:** inter-procedural analysis (track attribute access), or dynamic tracer fix for actual execution traces"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54888,"output":556,"cacheRead":11591,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67035,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774222143209}}
